      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Alejandrino G. Hufana (1926-2003) was a Filipino poet and author.  He taught English and creative writing at the 
	  University of the Philippines and was Director of the UP Creative Writing Center.  
	  He was a Rockefeller Foundation Fellow at the University of California at Berkeley (1961) and received a John D. Roosevelt 
	  III Fellowship in Art Librarianship at Columbia University (1969-1970) and a Research Fellowship of the National Libraryâ€™s 
	  Special Research Project (1974-78).  Other awards and recognitions include an outstanding Ilocano Writers and Journalists Award 
	  from the National Press Club (1980), the Tawid Awards for Arts &amp; Letters from the Ilocano Heritage Foundation (1981) and 
	  the Gawad Pambansang Alagad ni Balagtas from the Unyon ng mga Manunulat sa Pilipinas (1995).</p>
	  
	  <p>[Biographical sketch adapted from information found on the University of the Philippines website, 
	  <extref href="http://www.up.edu.ph/oldsystem/hufana.htm">http://www.up.edu.ph/oldsystem/hufana.htm</extref>.]</p></bioghist>
      
